,Not Recommended,231740,30763880,Posted: 26 March,all,AbominableAbdominal,"I really liked the design concept of the game. Ideally it gives you the freedom of exploring a vast, magical world and design your own adventure. It has the potential of becoming a tool kit for creative story telling with its pre-existing mechanics, however, that being said, all the stories within the game are all pre-written and quite limited. The game does a nice job in trying to replicate the feeling of being both in a real world and an imaginary one when playing DnD by allowing the player to purchase object in the ""real world"" with the gold you get in the game world while these items would aid you in games. The downside of this is that the game gets extremely grindy after some hours of playing. The characters of the game are relatively diverse, yet they only have 4 moves each, which makes the combat pattern repetitive.The style of the game is an 8-bit pixle art type, which is fine ---- gives me a feeling of Pokemon Leafgreen. The soundtrack of the game becomes really loopy, and seems rather limited.I would prehaps give the game a 6/10 as a decent time killer. A good game if on a discount (say for 3 or 4 dollars), but would not recommend buying for 10 dollars."
