,Not Recommended,231740,7804073,"Posted: 28 November, 2013",all,Disjecta Membra,"I picked up this game because it seemed to be a novel experience. Admittedly the first hour or so was very entertaining. The witty dialogue constantly breaks the fourth wall, and the Rollplay mechanics where fun for a while.Unfortunately the gameplay does not change very much after the first hour. The quests lack any distinction(the game breaks all quests down into a few archetypes), the progression system deteriorates into bland stat increases(each character has only 4 abilities), and the game's pacing entices the player to utilize the game's microtransactions to level quicker or buy better gear.There are unlockable characters, but to use them in the current playthrough you would need to spend some time leveling them from lvl 1 or use them in a a new playthrough.After a while the game slows to an almost literal grind. Enjoyment is derived by being able to jump in and out of over a VERY long period of time. Haven't beaten it yet but, it's pretty light and shallow so far."
