76561198082134101,Recommended,231740,10850635,"Posted: 26 June, 2014",all,ometreis,"This game is perfect for when I want something fun to distract me from real-life without having to put too much effort into it.  Basically you're controlling a tabletop group of people - DM included.  It's relaxing and turn-based - no button mashing required.  I love the dialog among the different characters you can play.  There are a lot of pop culture references and just enough crude humor to make it entertaining.  There are all sorts of upgrades you can buy with gold to decorate the room the group is playing in (rugs, doors, items for the table like loaded dice and books)  that give bonuses to your characters.  There's a lot of customization for the characters as well.  I got this on sale for $2, but I'd say it's worth the full price.  I can see myself playing this game for a long time."
