,Recommended,231740,9263674,"Posted: 25 February, 2014",all,Boyd the Reaver,"THE GOOD:-Basically the only DnD simulator on the market, at least to my knowledge-Tons of tongue in cheek humor and hilarious dialogue-Game shatters the fourth wall by the endgame, and it's glorious-Can choose which encounters you fight, which allows you to play at your own pace-Tons of freedom to choose your RL avatars and their DnD selves and classes-Ability to customize your room for all sorts of zany combinations-Overall a very fun - if easy - RPG romp with a unique twistTHE BAD:-Game's difficulty fluctuates often, and there are inconsistent difficulty spikes and ridiculously easy section-Microtransactions. Thankfully, this can be countered with Cheat Engine and some patience** = More on this later, if you're serious about buying the game.Here we have a short, but incredibly cute and fun game that's at least worth a shot to anybody who is a fan of DnD, JRPGs and tons of meta humor. To my knowledge, it's the only Dungeons and Dragons Simulator on Steam right now, at least to my knowledge, and the idea of being able to simulate a DnD game without the pain of finding people interested is EXTREMELY cool overall. As somebody who loves tabletop RPGs by seldom plays them due to the effort required to set them up on a regular basis, the very premise of this game was enough to sell me alone.And overall? It's a very good game. The story, which cliched, revels in it's clichedness, making tons of wisecracks at numerous genres, other games and making enough pop culture references to almost drown it it - and given the nature of this game, instead of being aggravating and forced, the DnD Simulator idea actually helps it work, overall making a stupidly enjoyable game that knows how dumb it is yet manages to make the best out of said idiocy.With solid gameplay, fine-tuned performance (then again, it's pretty damn hard to turn a retro RPG into an unplayable, buggy mess, but it happens) and a hilarious cast of zany characters, the game's only real major flaw is it's implication of microtransactions, in order to get more gold to buy more stuff. Normally this would seriously hurt the game since it demands some spending to be truly rich, but it backfires hilariously with Cheat Engine, as an increase from one penny to another means that you'll be able to use Cheat Engine to maintain a reasonably-fat wallet in-game.Overall, this is a fun, zany and stupidly enjoyable RPG with good writing, though I recommend you use Cheat Engine to enjoy it at it's fullest. Otherwise, give this game a go if you get the chance.For those too lazy to look up Cheat Engine:http://www.cheatengine.org/"
