,Recommended,231740,8849366,"Posted: 25 January, 2014",all,finaleve,"I picked this game for the concept alone.  A game about characters playing a tabletop RPG.  While the premise sounds promising, it doesn't exactly follow that format which would have turned this game into a sim of sorts.  What it does present is an amusing Turn Based RPG game of the old days, from classics like Dragon Warrior to D&D.As someone who actually played D&D for a few years, this game was rather appealing.  Select your team of generic players and their class (and will wear a matching hat for said class) and start an adventure.  The game provides you what most RPG games tend to have: a sense of direction.  You're provided with the main storyline and a few side-quests to pick up some extra gold and exp.Be warned, this game has micro-transactions.  It is not a vital aspect of the game as you can earn gold by farming but it's only optional.  I personally do not approve of it but that should not stop other people from doing so.  Your money.If you are looking for a charming, turn-based RPG that is a bit out of the ordinary, check this title out.  I'm enjoying it so far."
