,Recommended,231740,9059579,"Posted: 11 February, 2014",all,informer,"If you're an old school fan of Dungeons & Dragons and don't have the time to play an epic RPG, this game is for you. You do NOT need to buy any microtransactions in this game as long as you manage you money ok (read the guides and use +gold bonus modifiers). I like the fact that you have the option to play in different screen resolutions as well as in a windowed mode where you can multitask.This game takes turn-based RPG to its roots. Newer gamers may not appreciate it, but it is right for older gamers with busy lives. It is sprinkled with pop culture and various references throughout the game. It may get repetitive at times, but there are various classes to keep things fresh.The game doesn't do a very good job in explaining that you can mine rocks in caves for grindstone, and then take the stones to a town to raise the XP of the blacksmith. I would not suggest attempting to level up weapons and armors until later in the game since the success rate is so low. Reading the tips and guides will make your experience more enjoyable and you won't be wasting your hard-earned gold (since gold is used for everything, including travel)."
