76561198040996114,Recommended,231740,15471522,"Posted: 20 April, 2015",all,scrawford65,"I can't remember why exactly i bought this, nor do i care. This is a great game. I bought the five dollar expansion almost immediatly after playing a few missions because i didn't want to miss a thing.The game takes after DnD in that your players are a group of nerds at a table, being guided through an adventure by a GM. This opens up possibilities for excellent 4th wall breaks and humorous diolalogue, something the devs took full adventege of. The retro styles is pleasing to the eye and, just when i though i had beaten the game, a ton more suddenly opened up.The open endedness of the game was a huge selling point for me. There are clear idicators letting you know which way the plot lies, but you are free to explore wherever the heck you please. Suggestions are given for how strong you ought ot be before you go to different locations so you aren't unduely surprised when your two level ten boys are jumped by a level 25 wraith.There are cons of course. Items and items drops in general are poor, but gold is very easy to get ahold of while still making you work for it, so you can purchase the good items with moderate hassle. There is a fair amount of grinding, but it doesn't have to be samey if you don't let it. Honestly, this is a very good game and extremely well worth the price. 9.5/10."
