,Recommended,231740,351145,"Posted: 13 July, 2013",all,Aasha,"The game is advertised as you playing the *players* of people playing D&D. the gameplay honestly is just watered down D&D with the cast replaced by a table full of players though.It's a cute game for a bit. It cameos or references various topical humor bits liek Gremlins, Scooby Doo, Star wars, TMNT, Short Circut (the list goes on amazingly and would probably be the main reason to keep playing when the gameplay starts being a bore: Just to see what else they show us).But it doesn't really keep your interest too well as a game. The classes don't branch out or anything. Every class has the same 3 or 4 moves they started with. It also suffers from ""FF7 status effect syndrome""; where only pure damage and buff moves matter as anytime a debuff would be theoretically useful the monster is immune to it anyway - usually a boss, but not always.It's a cheap game though so you can't really go wrong if you just want to goof around and mess with something that doesn't take itself seriously. In small doses it's fun."
